A group, Asiwaju Bola Ahmad Tinubu Support Group (ABATSG), has called on Nigerians to ensure that they get there Permanent Voter’s Card (PVC) ahead of the 2023 general elections. The Plateau State Coordinator of ABATSG, Comrade Kasim Isa, told newsmen yesterday in Jos that there was need for Nigerians to make the right choice during the presidential poll. He said, “The current security situation, economy and others warrant intensive prayers for Nigeria and for Asiwaju Bola Ahmad Tinubu to succeed President Muhammadu Buhari in 2023.” The group also appealed to Nigerians, particularly youths, to ensure they get their PVC and vote wisely during the election. 